sentences: Born in New York, New York, he attended Queens College of the City University of New York, where he received his B.A. in 1947.
He later attended the Juilliard School of Music and, from 1949 to 1950, the Catholic University of Leuven.
He received his PhD from New York in 1960.
In 1963 he was taken on as a faculty member by the University of California at Davis and in 1971 became a music professor.

He moved to Northwestern University in 1973, where he was dean of the department until 1988 and a professor until his retirement in 1996.
